      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Continuum elastoplastic model (von Mises yield criterion, isotropic hardening, associative flow rule) selected for Ti-6Al-4V based on published literature and coupon-level material characterization (tensile tests per ASTM E8, N=5 coupons per lot). Model form assumptions — isotropy, rate-independence at 1–5 mm/min crosshead rate, no damage mechanics — are justified by the quasi-static loading regime and absence of fracture in validation specimens. Bone-substitute block (ultra-high molecular weight polyethylene, UHMWPE) modeled as linear elastic, justified by strain levels < 1% in block during test. Contact formulation: penalty-based with augmented Lagrangian for screw-rod interface; frictionless for fixture-block interface. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±3.5% on stiffness QoI via comparison of three constitutive model variants (bilinear, Ramberg-Osgood, multilinear).",
